Understanding Frozen Foods
Frozen foods encompass a broad category of food products preserved through freezing techniques to maintain nutritional integrity, texture, and flavor over extended periods. The modern frozen food sector spans:
Frozen fruits/vegetables (including IQF products)
Meat and seafood
Ready meals and pizza
Bakery products and desserts
Plant-based alternatives
The freezing process – whether through mechanical systems (-18°C to -40°C) or ultra-fast cryogenic methods (-196°C liquid nitrogen) – effectively halts microbial growth and enzymatic activity. While frozen food preservation traces back to ancient icehouse techniques, today's market thrives on advanced freezing technologies and sophisticated cold chain logistics.
